# Nginx with Docker - Quick Reference

## Objective
(in solar gencia instead ngix we  are using traffic for reverse proxy.traeffic avalable as a cotainer we can see  it in mmain org where prometheus connected to list metrics of trafic and all containers)
Learn how to:

- Pull the Nginx image
- Create an Nginx container
- Access the website
- Enter the container
- Understand the file structure
- Manage the container

---

# 1. Pull Nginx Image

```bash
docker pull nginx
```

Check downloaded images:

```bash
docker images
```

Example:

```
REPOSITORY   TAG       IMAGE ID
nginx        latest    xxxxxxxxx
```

---

# 2. Create Nginx Container

```bash
docker run -d --name nginx -p 80:80 nginx
```

Explanation

| Option | Meaning |
|---------|----------|
| docker run | Create and start a container |
| -d | Run in background (Detached mode) |
| --name nginx | Container name |
| -p 80:80 | Host Port 80 → Container Port 80 |
| nginx | Image name |

---

# 3. Verify Running Containers

```bash
docker ps
```

Example

```
CONTAINER ID   IMAGE    STATUS      PORTS
baaed21f872e   nginx    Up 2 mins   0.0.0.0:80->80/tcp
```

---

# 4. Open Website

Open browser

```
http://localhost
```

Expected output

```
Welcome to nginx!
```

---

# 5. Enter the Container

```bash
docker exec -it nginx bash
```

Prompt changes to

```
root@container-id:/#
```

You are now inside the Linux container.

---

# 6. Check Current User

```bash
whoami
```

Output

```
root
```

Check user details

```bash
id
```

Output

```
uid=0(root)
```

---

# 7. Explore Container

Root folders

```bash
ls /
```

Common folders

```
/etc
/usr
/var
/tmp
/home
/root
```

---

# 8. Go to Website Folder

```bash
cd /usr/share/nginx/html
```

List files

```bash
ls
```

Output

```
index.html
50x.html
```

---

# 9. View Default Web Page

```bash
cat index.html
```

This is the HTML shown at

```
http://localhost
```

---

# 10. Change Website

Replace page

```bash
echo "<h1>Hello Docker</h1>" > index.html
```

Refresh browser.

You will see

```
Hello Docker
```

---

# 11. Exit Container

```bash
exit
```

---

# 12. View Logs

```bash
docker logs nginx
```

---

# 13. Stop Container

```bash
docker stop nginx
```

---

# 14. Start Container

```bash
docker start nginx
```

---

# 15. Restart Container

```bash
docker restart nginx
```

---

# 16. Remove Container

Stop first

```bash
docker stop nginx
```

Remove

```bash
docker rm nginx
```

---

# 17. Remove Image

```bash
docker rmi nginx
```

---

# 18. Check Running Processes

```bash
docker top nginx
```

---

# 19. Inspect Container

```bash
docker inspect nginx
```

Shows

- IP Address
- Volumes
- Ports
- Networks
- Mounts
- Configuration

---

# 20. Container Statistics

```bash
docker stats
```

Shows

- CPU
- Memory
- Network
- Disk I/O

---

# Important Directories

| Directory | Purpose |
|------------|----------|
| /etc/nginx | Configuration |
| /usr/share/nginx/html | Website files |
| /var/log/nginx | Log files (if enabled) |
| /var/cache/nginx | Cache |
| /tmp | Temporary files |

---

# Nginx Architecture

```
Browser
    │
    ▼
Host Port 80
    │
    ▼
Docker Engine
    │
    ▼
Nginx Container
    │
    ▼
/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
```

---

# Why Use Nginx?

- Serve HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- Reverse Proxy
- HTTPS (SSL/TLS)
- Load Balancer
- Static Files
- API Gateway

---

# Reverse Proxy Example

```
Browser
    │
    ▼
Nginx
    │
    ├── Grafana
    ├── PHP API
    ├── Node-RED
    └── MQTT WebSocket
```

---

# Useful Docker Commands

```bash
docker images
docker ps
docker ps -a
docker logs nginx
docker exec -it nginx bash
docker inspect nginx
docker top nginx
docker stats
docker stop nginx
docker start nginx
docker restart nginx
docker rm nginx
```

